          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the pastry and blind bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the cold butter into the flour and icing sugar until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs. Mix in the egg yolk and 1 to 2 tablespoons of cold water to form a firm dough. Flatten into a disc, wrap, and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Preheat the oven to 200°C conventional. Roll the pastry to 3 mm thick and use it to line a 23 cm tart tin. Line with baking paper and fill with baking beans. Bake for 15 minutes, then remove the paper and beans and bake for a further 8 minutes until the base is fully dry and pale gold. Reduce the oven to 180°C.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and bake the filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt the golden syrup, brown sugar, and butter together in a saucepan over medium heat until the sugar dissolves. Remove from the heat and leave to cool for 10 minutes. Whisk in the eggs, vanilla, and salt. Scatter the pecan halves over the blind-baked case and pour the filling evenly over them; the pecans will float to the surface. Bake at 180°C for 35 to 40 minutes until the edges are set and the centre has a slight, uniform wobble. Leave to cool completely in the tin before slicing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
